the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Lorie, your role in this game is witch.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch used antidote to save Amado.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nAmado's speech: Good morning, everyone. I hope you all had a peaceful night. I want to start by thanking the Guard for their protection last night. It's crucial that we all work together to keep each other safe. As for the night itself, I didn't notice anything out of the ordinary, but I did observe some interesting interactions among the players. I think it's important that we all share our observations and listen to each other's perspectives before making any accusations. Let's try to gather more information and avoid jumping to conclusions. I believe that by working together and staying open-minded, we can identify the werewolves and ensure the village's survival.\nDonna's speech: Thank you, Amado, for your insightful words. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying open-minded. It's crucial that we gather as much information as possible before making any accusations. I believe that protecting key players like the Seer is essential for our survival. Let's be cautious and not jump to conclusions based on limited information. By working together and staying vigilant, we can identify the werewolves and ensure the village's safety.\nIsrael's speech: Thank you, Amado and Donna, for your wise words. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying open-minded. Last night, I didn't notice anything out of the ordinary, but I did observe some interesting interactions among the players. It's crucial that we all share our observations and listen to each other's perspectives before making any accusations. Let's try to gather more information and avoid jumping to conclusions. I believe that by working together and staying vigilant, we can identify the werewolves and ensure the village's safety. Additionally, I want to reiterate the importance of protecting key players like the Seer. By working together and staying united, we can overcome the werewolves and ensure the village's survival.\nJane's speech: Thank you, Amado, Donna, and Israel, for your insightful words. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying cautious. Last night, I didn't notice anything out of the ordinary, but I did observe some interesting interactions among the players. It's crucial that we all share our observations and listen to each other's perspectives before making any accusations. I believe that by working together and staying vigilant, we can identify the werewolves and ensure the village's safety. Additionally, I want to reiterate the importance of protecting key players like the Seer. By working together and staying united, we can overcome the werewolves and ensure the village's survival. Let's gather more information and avoid jumping to conclusions based on limited data.\nJanice's speech: Thank you, Amado, Donna, Israel, and Jane, for your insightful words. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying cautious. Last night, I didn't notice anything out of the ordinary, but I did observe some interesting interactions among the players. It's crucial that we all share our observations and listen to each other's perspectives before making any accusations. Let's try to gather more information and avoid jumping to 